    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MYTH OF COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>As one who has labored in the field of inner-city planning and housing for well over 40 years, I believe that Nicholas Lemann's "Myth of Community Development" (Jan. 9), with stunning economy, tells the whole story and separates the precious few grains of wheat from the enormous mound of chaff. He gives me hope that the coming generation may contend better with reality than we did.</p>
        <p>ROGER MONTGOMERY Dean, College of Environmental Design University of California Berkeley, Calif.</p>
      </block>
